parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Sludge Build-up
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to sludge build-up can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the oil light comes on
the engine knocks or makes a loud noise
the vehicle overheats
and there is a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to shut off without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning
the timing chain makes a loud noise
the engine stalls
and there is a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause the engine to shut off without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: A loud pop or explosion is heard
steam comes out of the grill and hood
and the engine shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the temperature gauge is in the red zone
and there is a loss of coolant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift interlock can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shift can be moved from park to drive without a key being in the ignition
the vehicle can jump out of gear and roll
the vehicle can shut down while driving
and the vehicle can surge forward before going into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle can downshift suddenly
causing a loss of power
the vehicle can hesitate or stumble when shifting
the transmission can slip or hesitate when shifting
and the vehicle can stall or shut down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle can shut down while driving
the vehicle can stall or hesitate when starting
and the check engine light can come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
